      <hedline>
        <hl1>In 50 States</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Monica Shaughnessy Hayden letter on W D Wetherell's June 4 travel article recalls her father's reaction to her 1979 trip through nine middle American states; drawing (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: W. D. Wetherell reminded me of a trip I made in 1979. Then, at the age of 39, having traveled alone all around the world, I realized I had been in only 41 states. So I decided to vacation in the nine states in middle America that I had missed. I flew out to Little Rock, Ark., and then zigzagged north, dutifully planting my feet in all of them.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: W. D. Wetherell reminded me of a trip I made in 1979. Then, at the age of 39, having traveled alone all around the world, I realized I had been in only 41 states. So I decided to vacation in the nine states in middle America that I had missed. I flew out to Little Rock, Ark., and then zigzagged north, dutifully planting my feet in all of them.</p>
        <p>Upon my return to New York, I boasted of my feat to my father. Pop's only comment was ''So what!''</p>
        <p>MONICA SHAUGHNESSY HAYDEN  Neponsit, Queens</p>
      </block>
